item.title: Undergrad
item.description: > undergrad I studied computer science and math at the University of Waterloo from Fall 2015 to Fall 2019. Here are some (unpolished) things I made during this time. notes live-LaTeXed course notes pmath351 - real analysis - Nico Spronk co471 - semidefinite optimization - Levent Tuncel personal projects terminal-jellies: implementation of Jelly no Puzzle variant with 3 custom levels syncflowy: prototype of a centralized workflowy + Google Docs crossover for collaborative nested list editing based on operational transform facial keypoint detection (github): implementation of One Millisecond Face Alignment with an Ensemble of Regression Trees (CVPR 2014) learning to compress neural networks in Caffe: handles fully connected layers only

item.title: Face Alignment Using Regression Trees
item.description: An implementation of Kazemi et al.‘s One Millisecond Face Alignment With An Ensemble of Regression Trees.
